	   <tr><td colspan=2>STA = hp<br><br>Casters at high level (especially int casters) have int coming out of their ears and start looking to maximize in other areas.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many int casters ignore ac (since a respectable 800ac isn't worth the sacrifice due to its negligent damage mitigation on uber mobs) and go for hp/mana/resists.<br><br>15 sta on an int caster equates to about 30hp.  About 45hp on a priest.  About 75hp on a hybrid.  About 90hp on a warrior.  (These are guesstimates for 60th level.  I'm a 60th cleric and get 3hp per stamina)  Why Verant didn't just slap +30hp onto it instead of +15 sta, I dunno.  But sta in the form of hp does have a use for int casters.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
